results.name: Number of numbers mapped to A127668(n) with the map described there.
comment: This is not A008481(n), n>=2, which starts similarly, but differs, beginning with n=24.
formula: a(n)<=pa(Length( A127668(n))), n>=2. Length gives the number of digits and pa(k):=A000041(k) (partition numbers). (It was originally claimed that this is equality, but that is not correct. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, May 21 2014)
example: a(4)=2 because two numbers are mapped to 11= A127668(4), namely n=p(1)*p(1)=4 and n=p(11)=31. p(n)=A000041(n) (partition numbers).
xref: The five numbers mapped to A127668(24)= 2111 are: 18433, 2594, 2263, 292, 24.
